# DIF concepts demonstration
demonstrate_dif_concepts <- function() {
  
  cat("=== DIF CONCEPTS DEMONSTRASIYASI ===\n")
  
  # Generate data with no DIF for comparison
  cat("Generating comparison datasets:\n")
  
  # Dataset 1: No DIF (Fair test)
  no_dif_data <- simulate_dif_data(n_focal = 400, n_reference = 600, n_items = 10, 
                                   dif_items = NULL, seed = 1111)
  
  # Dataset 2: With uniform DIF
  uniform_dif_data <- simulate_dif_data(n_focal = 400, n_reference = 600, n_items = 10, 
                                       dif_items = c(3, 7), dif_type = "uniform", 
                                       dif_size = 0.8, seed = 1111)
  
  # Dataset 3: With non-uniform DIF  
  nonuniform_dif_data <- simulate_dif_data(n_focal = 400, n_reference = 600, n_items = 10, 
                                           dif_items = c(5, 9), dif_type = "non-uniform", 
                                           dif_size = 0.6, seed = 1111)
  
  cat("Three datasets created:\n")
  cat("1. No DIF (fair test)\n")
  cat("2. Uniform DIF (items 3, 7)\n") 
  cat("3. Non-uniform DIF (items 5, 9)\n\n")
  
  # Basic group comparison
  cat("=== BASIC GROUP COMPARISONS ===\n")
  
  datasets <- list(
    "No DIF" = no_dif_data,
    "Uniform DIF" = uniform_dif_data, 
    "Non-uniform DIF" = nonuniform_dif_data
  )
  
  for(dataset_name in names(datasets)) {
    data_obj <- datasets[[dataset_name]]
    
    cat("\n", dataset_name, "Dataset:\n")
    
    # Group ability comparison
    ref_ability <- data_obj$theta[data_obj$group == "Reference"]
    focal_ability <- data_obj$theta[data_obj$group == "Focal"]
    
    cat("Reference group mean ability:", round(mean(ref_ability), 3), "\n")
    cat("Focal group mean ability:", round(mean(focal_ability), 3), "\n")
    
    # Total score comparison
    ref_scores <- rowSums(data_obj$data[data_obj$group == "Reference", ])
    focal_scores <- rowSums(data_obj$data[data_obj$group == "Focal", ])
    
    cat("Reference group mean total score:", round(mean(ref_scores), 2), "\n")
    cat("Focal group mean total score:", round(mean(focal_scores), 2), "\n")
    
    # Item-level differences
    ref_item_means <- colMeans(data_obj$data[data_obj$group == "Reference", ])
    focal_item_means <- colMeans(data_obj$data[data_obj$group == "Focal", ])
    
    item_differences <- focal_item_means - ref_item_means
    
    cat("Largest item difference:", round(max(abs(item_differences)), 3), 
        "for item", which.max(abs(item_differences)), "\n")
  }
  
  # Demonstrate impact vs bias
  cat("\n=== IMPACT VS BIAS DEMONSTRATION ===\n")
  
  impact_bias_explanation <- c(
    "**IMPACT (Acceptable):**",
    "â€¢ Real group differences in the construct being measured",
    "â€¢ Example: Different educational backgrounds leading to different math scores",
    "â€¢ Groups may perform differently due to genuine ability differences",
    "",
    "**BIAS (Unacceptable):**", 
    "â€¢ Measurement artifact that advantages/disadvantages certain groups",
    "â€¢ Example: Cultural references that are unfamiliar to some groups",
    "â€¢ Groups perform differently despite having same ability level",
    "",
    "**DIF Detection Goal:**",
    "â€¢ Identify bias while accounting for impact",
    "â€¢ Control for ability level when comparing groups",
    "â€¢ Ensure fair measurement across all populations"
  )
  
  for(line in impact_bias_explanation) {
    cat(line, "\n")
  }
  
  # Practical DIF detection preview
  cat("\n=== DIF DETECTION PREVIEW ===\n")
  
  # Quick DIF check using chi-square for demonstration
  quick_dif_check <- function(data, group, item_col) {
    
    # Create total score quintiles
    total_scores <- rowSums(data)
    score_quintiles <- cut(total_scores, breaks = 5, labels = FALSE)
    
    # Chi-square test within each quintile
    p_values <- numeric(5)
    
    for(q in 1:5) {
      quintile_mask <- score_quintiles == q
      if(sum(quintile_mask) > 10) {  # Sufficient sample size
        
        contingency_table <- table(
          data[quintile_mask, item_col],
          group[quintile_mask]
        )
        
        if(min(contingency_table) >= 5) {  # Chi-square assumptions
          chi_test <- chisq.test(contingency_table)
          p_values[q] <- chi_test$p.value
        } else {
          p_values[q] <- NA
        }
      } else {
        p_values[q] <- NA
      }
    }
    
    # Overall evidence
    mean_p <- mean(p_values, na.rm = TRUE)
    return(mean_p)
  }
  
  cat("Quick DIF screening (lower p-values suggest DIF):\n")
  
  for(dataset_name in names(datasets)) {
    data_obj <- datasets[[dataset_name]]
    
    cat(dataset_name, ":\n")
    
    for(item in 1:5) {  # Check first 5 items
      p_val <- quick_dif_check(data_obj$data, data_obj$group, item)
      cat("  Item", item, ": p =", 
          if(is.na(p_val)) "NA" else round(p_val, 4), "\n")
    }
  }
  
  cat("\nNote: This is a simplified screening. Proper DIF analysis follows.\n")
  
  return(datasets)
}

3 Uniform vs Non-uniform DIF

3.1 DIF NÃ¶vlÉ™rinin DetallÄ± Analizi vÉ™ VizuallaÅŸdÄ±rÄ±lmasÄ±

cat("=== UNIFORM VS NON-UNIFORM DIF ===\n\n")
## === UNIFORM VS NON-UNIFORM DIF ===
cat("Uniform DIF: Constant advantage/disadvantage across all ability levels\n")
## Uniform DIF: Constant advantage/disadvantage across all ability levels
cat("Non-uniform DIF: Advantage changes with ability level\n\n")
## Non-uniform DIF: Advantage changes with ability level
# Comprehensive uniform vs non-uniform DIF demonstration
demonstrate_uniform_vs_nonuniform_dif <- function() {
  
  cat("=== UNIFORM VS NON-UNIFORM DIF DEMONSTRASIYASI ===\n")
  
  # Generate specific examples for detailed comparison
  set.seed(2222)
  n_ref <- 500
  n_focal <- 300
  n_items <- 8
  
  # Example 1: Strong uniform DIF
  uniform_example <- simulate_dif_data(
    n_focal = n_focal, n_reference = n_ref, n_items = n_items,
    dif_items = c(3, 6), dif_type = "uniform", dif_size = 1.0
  )
  
  # Example 2: Strong non-uniform DIF
  nonuniform_example <- simulate_dif_data(
    n_focal = n_focal, n_reference = n_ref, n_items = n_items,
    dif_items = c(2, 7), dif_type = "non-uniform", dif_size = 0.8
  )
  
  # Example 3: Mixed DIF types
  mixed_example <- simulate_dif_data(
    n_focal = n_focal, n_reference = n_ref, n_items = n_items,
    dif_items = c(1, 4, 5), dif_type = "uniform", dif_size = 0.6
  )
  
  # Add non-uniform DIF to mixed example
  set.seed(2222)
  theta <- mixed_example$theta
  group <- mixed_example$group
  responses <- mixed_example$data
  
  # Manually add non-uniform DIF to item 8
  for(i in 1:length(theta)) {
    if(group[i] == "Focal") {
      # Non-uniform: higher discrimination for focal group
      a_new <- 2.5  # Increased discrimination
      b_new <- 0.5  # Slightly easier
      
      prob_new <- exp(a_new * (theta[i] - b_new)) / (1 + exp(a_new * (theta[i] - b_new)))
      responses[i, 8] <- rbinom(1, 1, prob_new)
    }
  }
  
  mixed_example$data <- responses
  mixed_example$true_params$dif_items <- c(1, 4, 5, 8)
  
  cat("Examples created:\n")
  cat("1. Uniform DIF (items 3, 6)\n")
  cat("2. Non-uniform DIF (items 2, 7)\n") 
  cat("3. Mixed DIF types (items 1, 4, 5 uniform; item 8 non-uniform)\n\n")
  
  # Detailed analysis for each type
  examples <- list(
    "Uniform DIF" = uniform_example,
    "Non-uniform DIF" = nonuniform_example,
    "Mixed DIF" = mixed_example
  )
  
  # Create comprehensive DIF plots
  if(require(ggplot2, quietly = TRUE)) {
    
    cat("=== VISUAL DIF ANALYSIS ===\n")
    
    plot_list <- list()
    
    for(example_name in names(examples)) {
      data_obj <- examples[[example_name]]
      
      cat("Creating plots for", example_name, "...\n")
      
      # Identify DIF items for this example
      if(example_name == "Uniform DIF") {
        dif_items_to_plot <- c(3, 6)
      } else if(example_name == "Non-uniform DIF") {
        dif_items_to_plot <- c(2, 7)
      } else {
        dif_items_to_plot <- c(1, 8)  # Show one uniform, one non-uniform
      }
      
      for(item in dif_items_to_plot) {
        plot_title <- paste(example_name, "- Item", item)
        p <- create_dif_plots(data_obj$data, data_obj$group, item, plot_title)
        
        if(!is.null(p)) {
          plot_list[[paste(example_name, "Item", item)]] <- p
        }
      }
    }
    
    # Display some key plots
    if(length(plot_list) > 0) {
      
      # Show uniform DIF example
      if("Uniform DIF Item 3" %in% names(plot_list)) {
        print(plot_list[["Uniform DIF Item 3"]])
      }
      
      # Show non-uniform DIF example  
      if("Non-uniform DIF Item 2" %in% names(plot_list)) {
        print(plot_list[["Non-uniform DIF Item 2"]])
      }
    }
  }
  
  # Quantitative analysis of DIF patterns
  cat("\n=== QUANTITATIVE DIF PATTERN ANALYSIS ===\n")
  
  analyze_dif_pattern <- function(data, group, item_col, title) {
    
    # Calculate ability-matched group differences
    total_scores <- rowSums(data)
    
    # Create ability bins
    ability_bins <- cut(total_scores, breaks = 5, labels = 1:5)
    
    # Calculate proportion correct by bin and group
    results <- data.frame()
    
    for(bin in 1:5) {
      bin_mask <- ability_bins == bin
      
      if(sum(bin_mask) > 5) {  # Sufficient sample
        ref_prop <- mean(data[bin_mask & group == "Reference", item_col], na.rm = TRUE)
        focal_prop <- mean(data[bin_mask & group == "Focal", item_col], na.rm = TRUE)
        
        difference <- focal_prop - ref_prop
        
        results <- rbind(results, data.frame(
          Bin = bin,
          Reference_Prop = round(ref_prop, 3),
          Focal_Prop = round(focal_prop, 3),
          Difference = round(difference, 3),
          Abs_Difference = round(abs(difference), 3)
        ))
      }
    }
    
    cat(title, ":\n")
    if(nrow(results) > 0) {
      print(results)
      
      # Pattern analysis
      dif_consistency <- sd(results$Difference, na.rm = TRUE)
      mean_dif <- mean(results$Difference, na.rm = TRUE)
      
      cat("Pattern analysis:\n")
      cat("  Mean DIF:", round(mean_dif, 3), "\n")
      cat("  DIF variability (SD):", round(dif_consistency, 3), "\n")
      
      if(dif_consistency < 0.05) {
        cat("  Pattern: UNIFORM DIF (consistent across ability levels)\n")
      } else if(dif_consistency < 0.10) {
        cat("  Pattern: MOSTLY UNIFORM DIF (some variation)\n")
      } else {
        cat("  Pattern: NON-UNIFORM DIF (varies across ability levels)\n")
      }
    } else {
      cat("  Insufficient data for analysis\n")
    }
    cat("\n")
    
    return(results)
  }
  
  # Analyze patterns for key items
  uniform_pattern <- analyze_dif_pattern(
    uniform_example$data, uniform_example$group, 3, "Uniform DIF Item 3"
  )
  
  nonuniform_pattern <- analyze_dif_pattern(
    nonuniform_example$data, nonuniform_example$group, 2, "Non-uniform DIF Item 2"
  )
  
  return(list(
    uniform_example = uniform_example,
    nonuniform_example = nonuniform_example,
    mixed_example = mixed_example,
    patterns = list(uniform = uniform_pattern, nonuniform = nonuniform_pattern)
  ))
}

# Run uniform vs non-uniform demonstration
dif_types_analysis <- demonstrate_uniform_vs_nonuniform_dif()

# Comprehensive DIF detection methods demonstration
demonstrate_dif_detection_methods <- function() {
  
  cat("=== COMPREHENSIVE DIF DETECTION ANALYSIS ===\n")
  
  # Use mixed DIF example from previous analysis
  if(exists("dif_types_analysis")) {
    test_data <- dif_types_analysis$mixed_example
  } else {
    # Create test data if not available
    test_data <- simulate_dif_data(
      n_focal = 300, n_reference = 500, n_items = 8,
      dif_items = c(2, 5, 7), dif_type = "uniform", dif_size = 0.8
    )
  }
  
  data_matrix <- test_data$data
  group_vector <- test_data$group
  
  cat("Test dataset:\n")
  cat("Reference group size:", sum(group_vector == "Reference"), "\n")
  cat("Focal group size:", sum(group_vector == "Focal"), "\n")
  cat("Number of items:", ncol(data_matrix), "\n")
  cat("Known DIF items:", paste(test_data$true_params$dif_items, collapse = ", "), "\n\n")
  
  # Method 1: Mantel-Haenszel using difR
  cat("=== METHOD 1: MANTEL-HAENSZEL ANALYSIS ===\n")
  
  if(require(difR, quietly = TRUE)) {
    
    tryCatch({
      # Prepare data for difR (needs specific format)
      group_numeric <- as.numeric(group_vector) - 1  # 0 = Reference, 1 = Focal
      
      # Mantel-Haenszel DIF detection
      mh_results <- difMH(
        Data = data_matrix,
        group = group_numeric,
        focal.name = 1,
        match = "score"  # Use total score for matching
      )
      
      cat("Mantel-Haenszel Results:\n")
      
      # Extract key results
      mh_summary <- data.frame(
        Item = paste0("Item", 1:ncol(data_matrix)),
        MH_Statistic = round(mh_results$MH, 3),
        p_value = round(mh_results$p.value, 4),
        Alpha_MH = round(mh_results$alphaMH, 3),
        DeltaMH = round(mh_results$deltaMH, 3),
        DIF_Flag = ifelse(mh_results$p.value < 0.05, "DIF", "No DIF")
      )
      
      print(mh_summary)
      
      cat("\nMH Interpretation:\n")
      cat("â€¢ MH > 1: Favors focal group\n")
      cat("â€¢ MH < 1: Favors reference group\n")
      cat("â€¢ |DeltaMH| > 1.5: Large DIF (ETS guidelines)\n")
      cat("â€¢ p < 0.05: Statistically significant\n\n")
      
      # Classification by effect size
      dif_items_mh <- which(mh_results$p.value < 0.05)
      large_dif_mh <- which(abs(mh_results$deltaMH) >= 1.5)
      
      cat("DIF flagged items (p < 0.05):", 
          if(length(dif_items_mh) > 0) paste(dif_items_mh, collapse = ", ") else "None", "\n")
      cat("Large effect DIF items (|Î”MH| â‰¥ 1.5):", 
          if(length(large_dif_mh) > 0) paste(large_dif_mh, collapse = ", ") else "None", "\n\n")
      
    }, error = function(e) {
      cat("Mantel-Haenszel analysis failed:", e$message, "\n\n")
      mh_summary <- NULL
    })
    
  } else {
    cat("difR package not available\n\n")
    mh_summary <- NULL
  }
  
  # Method 2: Logistic Regression (detailed analysis)
  cat("=== METHOD 2: LOGISTIC REGRESSION ANALYSIS ===\n")
  
  lr_results <- data.frame()
  
  for(item in 1:ncol(data_matrix)) {
    
    cat("Analyzing Item", item, "...\n")
    
    lr_analysis <- dif_logistic_regression(data_matrix, group_vector, item)
    
    # Extract results
    lr_results <- rbind(lr_results, data.frame(
      Item = item,
      Uniform_p = round(lr_analysis$uniform$p_value, 4),
      Uniform_R2 = round(lr_analysis$uniform$effect_size, 4),
      NonUniform_p = round(lr_analysis$nonuniform$p_value, 4),
      NonUniform_R2 = round(lr_analysis$nonuniform$effect_size, 4),
      Sample_Size = lr_analysis$sample_size
    ))
  }
  
  # Add DIF classification
  lr_results$Uniform_DIF <- ifelse(lr_results$Uniform_p < 0.05, 
                                   ifelse(lr_results$Uniform_R2 >= 0.035, "Large", "Moderate"), 
                                   "No DIF")
  
  lr_results$NonUniform_DIF <- ifelse(lr_results$NonUniform_p < 0.05, 
                                      ifelse(lr_results$NonUniform_R2 >= 0.035, "Large", "Moderate"), 
                                      "No DIF")
  
  cat("\nLogistic Regression Results:\n")
  print(lr_results)
  
  cat("\nLR Interpretation (ETS Guidelines):\n")
  cat("â€¢ p < 0.05: Statistically significant DIF\n")
  cat("â€¢ RÂ² < 0.035: Negligible effect (Category A)\n")
  cat("â€¢ 0.035 â‰¤ RÂ² < 0.070: Moderate effect (Category B)\n")
  cat("â€¢ RÂ² â‰¥ 0.070: Large effect (Category C)\n\n")
  
  # Method 3: Lord's Chi-square (if possible with available packages)
  cat("=== METHOD 3: IRT-BASED DIF DETECTION ===\n")
  
  if(require(mirt, quietly = TRUE)) {
    
    tryCatch({
      
      # Fit separate IRT models for each group
      ref_data <- data_matrix[group_vector == "Reference", ]
      focal_data <- data_matrix[group_vector == "Focal", ]
      
      # Fit 2PL models
      ref_model <- mirt(ref_data, 1, itemtype = "2PL", verbose = FALSE)
      focal_model <- mirt(focal_data, 1, itemtype = "2PL", verbose = FALSE)
      
      # Extract item parameters
      ref_params <- coef(ref_model, simplify = TRUE)$items
      focal_params <- coef(focal_model, simplify = TRUE)$items
      
      # Calculate parameter differences
      a_diff <- focal_params[, "a1"] - ref_params[, "a1"]
      b_diff <- (focal_params[, "d"] / (-focal_params[, "a1"])) - 
                (ref_params[, "d"] / (-ref_params[, "a1"]))
      
      irt_comparison <- data.frame(
        Item = 1:ncol(data_matrix),
        Ref_Discrimination = round(ref_params[, "a1"], 3),
        Focal_Discrimination = round(focal_params[, "a1"], 3),
        Discrimination_Diff = round(a_diff, 3),
        Ref_Difficulty = round(ref_params[, "d"] / (-ref_params[, "a1"]), 3),
        Focal_Difficulty = round(focal_params[, "d"] / (-focal_params[, "a1"]), 3),
        Difficulty_Diff = round(b_diff, 3)
      )
      
      cat("IRT Parameter Comparison:\n")
      print(irt_comparison)
      
      cat("\nIRT-based DIF indicators:\n")
      cat("â€¢ Large discrimination differences suggest non-uniform DIF\n")
      cat("â€¢ Large difficulty differences suggest uniform DIF\n")
      cat("â€¢ |Difficulty difference| > 0.5 often considered substantial\n\n")
      
      # Flag potential DIF items
      irt_dif_items <- which(abs(irt_comparison$Difficulty_Diff) > 0.5 | 
                            abs(irt_comparison$Discrimination_Diff) > 0.3)
      
      cat("IRT-flagged DIF items:", 
          if(length(irt_dif_items) > 0) paste(irt_dif_items, collapse = ", ") else "None", "\n\n")
      
    }, error = function(e) {
      cat("IRT-based analysis failed:", e$message, "\n\n")
      irt_comparison <- NULL
      irt_dif_items <- NULL
    })
    
  } else {
    cat("mirt package not available for IRT analysis\n\n")
    irt_comparison <- NULL
    irt_dif_items <- NULL
  }
  
  # Method comparison and consensus
  cat("=== METHOD COMPARISON AND CONSENSUS ===\n")
  
  # Create comparison table
  method_comparison <- data.frame(
    Item = 1:ncol(data_matrix),
    True_DIF = 1:ncol(data_matrix) %in% test_data$true_params$dif_items,
    MH_Flag = if(exists("mh_summary") && !is.null(mh_summary)) mh_summary$DIF_Flag == "DIF" else NA,
    LR_Uniform = lr_results$Uniform_DIF != "No DIF",
    LR_NonUniform = lr_results$NonUniform_DIF != "No DIF",
    IRT_Flag = if(exists("irt_dif_items") && !is.null(irt_dif_items)) 1:ncol(data_matrix) %in% irt_dif_items else NA
  )
  
  # Count agreements
  method_comparison$Total_Methods <- rowSums(method_comparison[, c("MH_Flag", "LR_Uniform", "LR_NonUniform", "IRT_Flag")], na.rm = TRUE)
  method_comparison$Consensus <- method_comparison$Total_Methods >= 2
  
  cat("Method Comparison:\n")
  print(method_comparison)
  
  # Performance evaluation
  if(any(!is.na(method_comparison$MH_Flag))) {
    
    cat("\nMethod Performance Evaluation:\n")
    
    methods <- c("MH_Flag", "LR_Uniform", "LR_NonUniform", "IRT_Flag", "Consensus")
    
    for(method in methods) {
      if(!all(is.na(method_comparison[[method]]))) {
        
        method_flags <- method_comparison[[method]]
        true_dif <- method_comparison$True_DIF
        
        # Calculate performance metrics
        tp <- sum(method_flags & true_dif, na.rm = TRUE)  # True positives
        fp <- sum(method_flags & !true_dif, na.rm = TRUE)  # False positives
        tn <- sum(!method_flags & !true_dif, na.rm = TRUE)  # True negatives
        fn <- sum(!method_flags & true_dif, na.rm = TRUE)  # False negatives
        
        sensitivity <- if(tp + fn > 0) tp / (tp + fn) else NA
        specificity <- if(tn + fp > 0) tn / (tn + fp) else NA
        accuracy <- if(tp + fp + tn + fn > 0) (tp + tn) / (tp + fp + tn + fn) else NA
        
        cat(method, ":\n")
        cat("  Sensitivity (true positive rate):", round(sensitivity, 3), "\n")
        cat("  Specificity (true negative rate):", round(specificity, 3), "\n")
        cat("  Overall accuracy:", round(accuracy, 3), "\n")
      }
    }
  }
  
  return(list(
    data = test_data,
    mh_results = if(exists("mh_summary")) mh_summary else NULL,
    lr_results = lr_results,
    irt_results = if(exists("irt_comparison")) irt_comparison else NULL,
    method_comparison = method_comparison
  ))
}

# Run comprehensive DIF detection methods analysis
dif_methods_analysis <- demonstrate_dif_detection_methods()

## Mantel-Haenszel: Classical approach for DIF detection
cat("â€¢ Controls for ability using total score matching\n")
## â€¢ Controls for ability using total score matching

## â€¢ Provides odds ratio (Alpha MH) and effect size (Delta MH)

## â€¢ Well-established guidelines for interpretation
# Detailed Mantel-Haenszel demonstration
demonstrate_mantel_haenszel_detailed <- function() {
  
  cat("=== DETAILED MANTEL-HAENSZEL ANALYSIS ===\n")
  
  # Create specific example with known DIF
  set.seed(3333)
  mh_example <- simulate_dif_data(
    n_focal = 400, n_reference = 600, n_items = 12,
    dif_items = c(3, 7, 10), dif_type = "uniform", dif_size = 1.2
  )
  
  data_matrix <- mh_example$data
  group_vector <- mh_example$group
  
  cat("MH Example Dataset:\n")
  cat("Sample sizes: Reference =", sum(group_vector == "Reference"), 
      ", Focal =", sum(group_vector == "Focal"), "\n")
  cat("Items with DIF:", paste(mh_example$true_params$dif_items, collapse = ", "), "\n\n")
  
  # Manual Mantel-Haenszel calculation for educational purposes
  manual_mh_calculation <- function(data, group, item_col) {
    
    # Calculate total scores for matching
    total_scores <- rowSums(data)
    
    # Create score intervals
    score_range <- range(total_scores)
    score_intervals <- seq(score_range[1], score_range[2], by = 1)
    
    # Initialize MH statistics
    mh_numerator <- 0
    mh_denominator <- 0
    var_log_mh <- 0
    
    for(score in score_intervals) {
      
      # Get individuals with this total score
      score_mask <- total_scores == score
      
      if(sum(score_mask) >= 4) {  # Minimum for stable estimates
        
        # Create 2x2 contingency table for this score level
        score_data <- data[score_mask, ]
        score_group <- group[score_mask]
        
        # Contingency table: rows = item response, cols = group
        a <- sum(score_data[, item_col] == 1 & score_group == "Focal")     # Focal correct
        b <- sum(score_data[, item_col] == 1 & score_group == "Reference") # Reference correct
        c <- sum(score_data[, item_col] == 0 & score_group == "Focal")     # Focal incorrect
        d <- sum(score_data[, item_col] == 0 & score_group == "Reference") # Reference incorrect
        
        # Total counts
        n_focal <- a + c
        n_ref <- b + d
        n_correct <- a + b
        n_total <- a + b + c + d
        
        if(n_total > 0 && n_focal > 0 && n_ref > 0) {
          
          # Expected value under null hypothesis
          expected_a <- (n_focal * n_correct) / n_total
          
          # MH components
          mh_numerator <- mh_numerator + (a - expected_a)
          mh_denominator <- mh_denominator + (a * d) / n_total
          
          # Variance component
          if(n_total > 1) {
            var_component <- (n_focal * n_ref * n_correct * (n_total - n_correct)) / 
                           (n_total^2 * (n_total - 1))
            var_log_mh <- var_log_mh + var_component
          }
        }
      }
    }
    
    # Calculate MH statistics
    if(mh_denominator > 0) {
      alpha_mh <- (mh_numerator + mh_denominator) / mh_denominator
      delta_mh <- -2.35 * log(alpha_mh)  # ETS Delta scale
      
      # Chi-square test
      if(var_log_mh > 0) {
        mh_chi_square <- (abs(mh_numerator) - 0.5)^2 / var_log_mh  # Continuity correction
        p_value <- 1 - pchisq(mh_chi_square, df = 1)
      } else {
        mh_chi_square <- NA
        p_value <- NA
      }
      
    } else {
      alpha_mh <- NA
      delta_mh <- NA
      mh_chi_square <- NA
      p_value <- NA
    }
    
    return(list(
      alpha_mh = alpha_mh,
      delta_mh = delta_mh,
      chi_square = mh_chi_square,
      p_value = p_value
    ))
  }
  
  # Perform manual MH calculation for demonstration
  cat("=== MANUAL MH CALCULATION (Educational) ===\n")
  
  manual_results <- data.frame()
  
  for(item in c(3, 7, 10, 5)) {  # DIF items + one non-DIF item
    
    mh_calc <- manual_mh_calculation(data_matrix, group_vector, item)
    
    manual_results <- rbind(manual_results, data.frame(
      Item = item,
      Alpha_MH = round(mh_calc$alpha_mh, 3),
      Delta_MH = round(mh_calc$delta_mh, 3),
      Chi_Square = round(mh_calc$chi_square, 3),
      p_value = round(mh_calc$p_value, 4),
      Expected_DIF = item %in% mh_example$true_params$dif_items
    ))
  }
  
  cat("Manual MH Results (Sample Items):\n")
  print(manual_results)
  
  # Full analysis using difR package
  cat("\n=== COMPREHENSIVE MH ANALYSIS WITH difR ===\n")
  
  if(require(difR, quietly = TRUE)) {
    
    tryCatch({
      
      # Convert group to numeric (difR requirement)
      group_numeric <- as.numeric(group_vector) - 1
      
      # Comprehensive MH analysis
      mh_full <- difMH(
        Data = data_matrix,
        group = group_numeric,
        focal.name = 1,
        match = "score",
        correct = TRUE,  # Continuity correction
        purify = FALSE   # Don't purify for this demonstration
      )
      
      # Create comprehensive results table
      mh_comprehensive <- data.frame(
        Item = paste0("Item", 1:ncol(data_matrix)),
        Alpha_MH = round(mh_full$alphaMH, 3),
        Delta_MH = round(mh_full$deltaMH, 3),
        MH_Statistic = round(mh_full$MH, 3),
        p_value = round(mh_full$p.value, 4),
        True_DIF = 1:ncol(data_matrix) %in% mh_example$true_params$dif_items
      )
      
      # Add effect size classification
      mh_comprehensive$Effect_Size <- ifelse(
        abs(mh_comprehensive$Delta_MH) < 1.0, "Negligible",
        ifelse(abs(mh_comprehensive$Delta_MH) < 1.5, "Moderate", "Large")
      )
      
      # Add statistical significance
      mh_comprehensive$Significant <- ifelse(mh_comprehensive$p_value < 0.05, "Yes", "No")
      
      # Add DIF direction
      mh_comprehensive$DIF_Direction <- ifelse(
        mh_comprehensive$Delta_MH > 0, "Favors Reference",
        ifelse(mh_comprehensive$Delta_MH < 0, "Favors Focal", "No DIF")
      )
      
      cat("Comprehensive MH Results:\n")
      print(mh_comprehensive)
      
      # Summary statistics
      cat("\nMH Analysis Summary:\n")
      cat("Items with significant DIF (p < 0.05):", 
          sum(mh_comprehensive$Significant == "Yes"), "\n")
      cat("Items with large effect DIF (|Î”MH| â‰¥ 1.5):", 
          sum(mh_comprehensive$Effect_Size == "Large"), "\n")
      cat("Items favoring reference group:", 
          sum(mh_comprehensive$Delta_MH > 1.0), "\n")
      cat("Items favoring focal group:", 
          sum(mh_comprehensive$Delta_MH < -1.0), "\n")
      
      # Detection accuracy
      detected_dif <- which(mh_comprehensive$p_value < 0.05)
      true_dif <- mh_example$true_params$dif_items
      
      true_positives <- length(intersect(detected_dif, true_dif))
      false_positives <- length(setdiff(detected_dif, true_dif))
      false_negatives <- length(setdiff(true_dif, detected_dif))
      
      sensitivity <- true_positives / length(true_dif)
      precision <- if(length(detected_dif) > 0) true_positives / length(detected_dif) else 0
      
      cat("\nDetection Performance:\n")
      cat("Sensitivity (true positive rate):", round(sensitivity, 3), "\n")
      cat("Precision (positive predictive value):", round(precision, 3), "\n")
      cat("True positives:", true_positives, "\n")
      cat("False positives:", false_positives, "\n")
      cat("False negatives:", false_negatives, "\n")
      
    }, error = function(e) {
      cat("difR MH analysis failed:", e$message, "\n")
      mh_comprehensive <- NULL
    })
    
  } else {
    cat("difR package not available\n")
    mh_comprehensive <- NULL
  }
  
  # MH interpretation guidelines
  cat("\n=== MH INTERPRETATION GUIDELINES ===\n")
  
  interpretation_guide <- c(
    "**ALPHA MH INTERPRETATION:**",
    "â€¢ Alpha MH = 1.0: No DIF",
    "â€¢ Alpha MH > 1.0: Item easier for focal group",
    "â€¢ Alpha MH < 1.0: Item easier for reference group",
    "â€¢ Values far from 1.0 indicate stronger DIF",
    "",
    "**DELTA MH INTERPRETATION (ETS Guidelines):**",
    "â€¢ |Î”MH| < 1.0: Negligible DIF (Category A)",
    "â€¢ 1.0 â‰¤ |Î”MH| < 1.5: Moderate DIF (Category B)", 
    "â€¢ |Î”MH| â‰¥ 1.5: Large DIF (Category C)",
    "â€¢ Positive Î”MH: Favors reference group",
    "â€¢ Negative Î”MH: Favors focal group",
    "",
    "**STATISTICAL SIGNIFICANCE:**",
    "â€¢ p < 0.05: Statistically significant DIF",
    "â€¢ Consider both p-value AND effect size",
    "â€¢ Large samples may yield significant but negligible DIF",
    "",
    "**PRACTICAL DECISIONS:**",
    "â€¢ Category A: Usually retain item",
    "â€¢ Category B: Review content, consider revision",
    "â€¢ Category C: Strong candidate for revision or removal",
    "â€¢ Always combine statistical analysis with expert review"
  )
  
  for(guideline in interpretation_guide) {
    cat(guideline, "\n")
  }
  
  return(list(
    data = mh_example,
    manual_results = manual_results,
    comprehensive_results = if(exists("mh_comprehensive")) mh_comprehensive else NULL
  ))
}

cat("Logistic Regression: Flexible and powerful DIF detection method\n")
## Logistic Regression: Flexible and powerful DIF detection method

# Comprehensive logistic regression DIF analysis
demonstrate_logistic_regression_comprehensive <- function() {
  
  cat("=== COMPREHENSIVE LOGISTIC REGRESSION DIF ANALYSIS ===\n")
  
  # Create diverse DIF example
  set.seed(4444)
  lr_example <- simulate_dif_data(
    n_focal = 500, n_reference = 800, n_items = 15,
    dif_items = c(3, 7, 11, 14), dif_type = "uniform", dif_size = 0.9
  )
  
  # Add non-uniform DIF to some items
  data_matrix <- lr_example$data
  group_vector <- lr_example$group
  theta <- lr_example$theta
  
  # Manually create non-uniform DIF for items 5 and 12
  for(i in 1:length(theta)) {
    if(group_vector[i] == "Focal") {
      
      # Item 5: Non-uniform DIF (higher discrimination for focal group)
      a_new_5 <- 2.8
      b_new_5 <- 0.3
      prob_new_5 <- exp(a_new_5 * (theta[i] - b_new_5)) / (1 + exp(a_new_5 * (theta[i] - b_new_5)))
      data_matrix[i, 5] <- rbinom(1, 1, prob_new_5)
      
      # Item 12: Crossing DIF (complex interaction)
      if(theta[i] < 0) {
        # Low ability focal group disadvantaged
        prob_new_12 <- exp(1.0 * (theta[i] - 1.2)) / (1 + exp(1.0 * (theta[i] - 1.2)))
      } else {
        # High ability focal group advantaged
        prob_new_12 <- exp(2.2 * (theta[i] + 0.5)) / (1 + exp(2.2 * (theta[i] + 0.5)))
      }
      data_matrix[i, 12] <- rbinom(1, 1, prob_new_12)
    }
  }
  
  # Update the data object
  lr_example$data <- data_matrix
  lr_example$true_params$dif_items <- c(3, 5, 7, 11, 12, 14)
  lr_example$true_params$uniform_dif <- c(3, 7, 11, 14)
  lr_example$true_params$nonuniform_dif <- c(5, 12)
  
  cat("LR Example Dataset:\n")
  cat("Sample sizes: Reference =", sum(group_vector == "Reference"), 
      ", Focal =", sum(group_vector == "Focal"), "\n")
  cat("Uniform DIF items:", paste(lr_example$true_params$uniform_dif, collapse = ", "), "\n")
  cat("Non-uniform DIF items:", paste(lr_example$true_params$nonuniform_dif, collapse = ", "), "\n\n")
  
  # Comprehensive logistic regression analysis
  cat("=== DETAILED LOGISTIC REGRESSION ANALYSIS ===\n")
  
  lr_comprehensive_results <- data.frame()
  
  for(item in 1:ncol(data_matrix)) {
    
    cat("Analyzing Item", item, "...\n")
    
    # Enhanced logistic regression analysis
    enhanced_lr_analysis <- function(data, group, item_col) {
      
      # Multiple matching strategies
      total_score <- rowSums(data, na.rm = TRUE)
      rest_score <- rowSums(data[, -item_col], na.rm = TRUE)
      
      # Prepare variables
      item_response <- data[, item_col]
      group_numeric <- as.numeric(group) - 1
      
      # Remove missing values
      complete_cases <- complete.cases(item_response, group_numeric, total_score, rest_score)
      
      if(sum(complete_cases) < 20) {
        return(list(error = "Insufficient data"))
      }
      
      item_response <- item_response[complete_cases]
      group_numeric <- group_numeric[complete_cases]
      total_score <- total_score[complete_cases]
      rest_score <- rest_score[complete_cases]
      
      # Standardize matching variables for better interpretation
      total_score_std <- scale(total_score)[,1]
      rest_score_std <- scale(rest_score)[,1]
      
      # Model fitting with different matching strategies
      results <- list()
      
      # Strategy 1: Total score matching
      model0_total <- glm(item_response ~ total_score_std, family = binomial())
      model1_total <- glm(item_response ~ total_score_std + group_numeric, family = binomial())
      model2_total <- glm(item_response ~ total_score_std + group_numeric + total_score_std:group_numeric, family = binomial())
      
      # Strategy 2: Rest score matching
      model0_rest <- glm(item_response ~ rest_score_std, family = binomial())
      model1_rest <- glm(item_response ~ rest_score_std + group_numeric, family = binomial())
      model2_rest <- glm(item_response ~ rest_score_std + group_numeric + rest_score_std:group_numeric, family = binomial())
      
      # Calculate effect sizes (Nagelkerke RÂ²)
      nagelkerke_r2 <- function(model_full, model_reduced) {
        ll_full <- logLik(model_full)
        ll_reduced <- logLik(model_reduced)
        n <- nobs(model_full)
        
        cox_snell <- 1 - exp((2/n) * (ll_reduced - ll_full))
        max_r2 <- 1 - exp((2/n) * ll_reduced)
        nagelkerke <- cox_snell / max_r2
        
        return(as.numeric(nagelkerke))
      }
      
      # Total score results
      uniform_r2_total <- nagelkerke_r2(model1_total, model0_total)
      nonuniform_r2_total <- nagelkerke_r2(model2_total, model1_total)
      
      lrt_uniform_total <- anova(model0_total, model1_total, test = "Chisq")
      lrt_nonuniform_total <- anova(model1_total, model2_total, test = "Chisq")
      
      uniform_p_total <- lrt_uniform_total$`Pr(>Chi)`[2]
      nonuniform_p_total <- lrt_nonuniform_total$`Pr(>Chi)`[2]
      
      # Rest score results
      uniform_r2_rest <- nagelkerke_r2(model1_rest, model0_rest)
      nonuniform_r2_rest <- nagelkerke_r2(model2_rest, model1_rest)
      
      lrt_uniform_rest <- anova(model0_rest, model1_rest, test = "Chisq")
      lrt_nonuniform_rest <- anova(model1_rest, model2_rest, test = "Chisq")
      
      uniform_p_rest <- lrt_uniform_rest$`Pr(>Chi)`[2]
      nonuniform_p_rest <- lrt_nonuniform_rest$`Pr(>Chi)`[2]
      
      # Extract coefficients for interpretation
      group_coef_total <- coef(model1_total)["group_numeric"]
      interaction_coef_total <- coef(model2_total)["total_score_std:group_numeric"]
      
      return(list(
        total_score = list(
          uniform_p = uniform_p_total,
          uniform_r2 = uniform_r2_total,
          nonuniform_p = nonuniform_p_total,
          nonuniform_r2 = nonuniform_r2_total,
          group_coef = group_coef_total,
          interaction_coef = interaction_coef_total
        ),
        rest_score = list(
          uniform_p = uniform_p_rest,
          uniform_r2 = uniform_r2_rest,
          nonuniform_p = nonuniform_p_rest,
          nonuniform_r2 = nonuniform_r2_rest
        ),
        sample_size = length(item_response)
      ))
    }
    
    # Perform enhanced analysis
    lr_analysis <- enhanced_lr_analysis(data_matrix, group_vector, item)
    
    if("error" %in% names(lr_analysis)) {
      next  # Skip items with insufficient data
    }
    
    # Extract results (using total score matching as primary)
    lr_comprehensive_results <- rbind(lr_comprehensive_results, data.frame(
      Item = item,
      
      # Total score matching results
      Uniform_p_Total = round(lr_analysis$total_score$uniform_p, 4),
      Uniform_R2_Total = round(lr_analysis$total_score$uniform_r2, 4),
      NonUniform_p_Total = round(lr_analysis$total_score$nonuniform_p, 4),
      NonUniform_R2_Total = round(lr_analysis$total_score$nonuniform_r2, 4),
      
      # Rest score matching results
      Uniform_p_Rest = round(lr_analysis$rest_score$uniform_p, 4),
      Uniform_R2_Rest = round(lr_analysis$rest_score$uniform_r2, 4),
      NonUniform_p_Rest = round(lr_analysis$rest_score$nonuniform_p, 4),
      NonUniform_R2_Rest = round(lr_analysis$rest_score$nonuniform_r2, 4),
      
      # Coefficients
      Group_Coef = round(lr_analysis$total_score$group_coef, 3),
      Interaction_Coef = round(lr_analysis$total_score$interaction_coef, 3),
      
      Sample_Size = lr_analysis$sample_size
    ))
  }
  
  # Add DIF classifications
  lr_comprehensive_results$Uniform_DIF <- with(lr_comprehensive_results, 
    ifelse(Uniform_p_Total < 0.05,
           ifelse(Uniform_R2_Total >= 0.070, "Large",
                  ifelse(Uniform_R2_Total >= 0.035, "Moderate", "Small")),
           "No DIF"))
  
  lr_comprehensive_results$NonUniform_DIF <- with(lr_comprehensive_results,
    ifelse(NonUniform_p_Total < 0.05,
           ifelse(NonUniform_R2_Total >= 0.070, "Large", 
                  ifelse(NonUniform_R2_Total >= 0.035, "Moderate", "Small")),
           "No DIF"))
  
  # Add true DIF status
  lr_comprehensive_results$True_Uniform <- lr_comprehensive_results$Item %in% lr_example$true_params$uniform_dif
  lr_comprehensive_results$True_NonUniform <- lr_comprehensive_results$Item %in% lr_example$true_params$nonuniform_dif
  
  cat("\nComprehensive Logistic Regression Results:\n")
  print(lr_comprehensive_results[, c("Item", "Uniform_p_Total", "Uniform_R2_Total", 
                                    "NonUniform_p_Total", "NonUniform_R2_Total", 
                                    "Uniform_DIF", "NonUniform_DIF")])
  
  # Summary analysis
  cat("\n=== DIF DETECTION SUMMARY ===\n")
  
  uniform_detected <- lr_comprehensive_results$Uniform_DIF %in% c("Small", "Moderate", "Large")
  nonuniform_detected <- lr_comprehensive_results$NonUniform_DIF %in% c("Small", "Moderate", "Large")
  
  cat("Items with uniform DIF detected:", sum(uniform_detected), "\n")
  cat("Items with non-uniform DIF detected:", sum(nonuniform_detected), "\n")
  cat("Items with large effect DIF (any type):", 
      sum(lr_comprehensive_results$Uniform_DIF == "Large" | lr_comprehensive_results$NonUniform_DIF == "Large"), "\n")
  
  # Performance evaluation
  cat("\n=== DETECTION PERFORMANCE EVALUATION ===\n")
  
  # Uniform DIF detection performance
  true_uniform <- lr_comprehensive_results$True_Uniform
  detected_uniform <- uniform_detected
  
  tp_uniform <- sum(detected_uniform & true_uniform)
  fp_uniform <- sum(detected_uniform & !true_uniform)
  fn_uniform <- sum(!detected_uniform & true_uniform)
  tn_uniform <- sum(!detected_uniform & !true_uniform)
  
  sens_uniform <- tp_uniform / (tp_uniform + fn_uniform)
  spec_uniform <- tn_uniform / (tn_uniform + fp_uniform)
  prec_uniform <- if(tp_uniform + fp_uniform > 0) tp_uniform / (tp_uniform + fp_uniform) else 0
  
  cat("Uniform DIF Detection:\n")
  cat("  Sensitivity:", round(sens_uniform, 3), "\n")
  cat("  Specificity:", round(spec_uniform, 3), "\n")
  cat("  Precision:", round(prec_uniform, 3), "\n")
  
  # Non-uniform DIF detection performance  
  true_nonuniform <- lr_comprehensive_results$True_NonUniform
  detected_nonuniform <- nonuniform_detected
  
  tp_nonuniform <- sum(detected_nonuniform & true_nonuniform)
  fp_nonuniform <- sum(detected_nonuniform & !true_nonuniform)
  fn_nonuniform <- sum(!detected_nonuniform & true_nonuniform)
  tn_nonuniform <- sum(!detected_nonuniform & !true_nonuniform)
  
  sens_nonuniform <- if(tp_nonuniform + fn_nonuniform > 0) tp_nonuniform / (tp_nonuniform + fn_nonuniform) else 0
  spec_nonuniform <- tn_nonuniform / (tn_nonuniform + fp_nonuniform)
  prec_nonuniform <- if(tp_nonuniform + fp_nonuniform > 0) tp_nonuniform / (tp_nonuniform + fp_nonuniform) else 0
  
  cat("Non-uniform DIF Detection:\n")
  cat("  Sensitivity:", round(sens_nonuniform, 3), "\n")
  cat("  Specificity:", round(spec_nonuniform, 3), "\n")
  cat("  Precision:", round(prec_nonuniform, 3), "\n")
  
  # Create detailed plots for selected items
  if(require(ggplot2, quietly = TRUE)) {
    
    cat("\n=== CREATING DIF VISUALIZATION ===\n")
    
    # Plot items with different DIF types
    items_to_plot <- c(3, 5, 12, 8)  # Uniform, non-uniform, crossing, no DIF
    plot_list <- list()
    
    for(item in items_to_plot) {
      if(item <= ncol(data_matrix)) {
        
        # Determine DIF type for title
        dif_type <- "No DIF"
        if(item %in% lr_example$true_params$uniform_dif) dif_type <- "Uniform DIF"
        if(item %in% lr_example$true_params$nonuniform_dif) dif_type <- "Non-uniform DIF"
        
        plot_title <- paste("Item", item, "-", dif_type)
        p <- create_dif_plots(data_matrix, group_vector, item, plot_title)
        
        if(!is.null(p)) {
          plot_list[[paste("Item", item)]] <- p
          print(p)  # Display each plot
        }
      }
    }
  }
  
  return(list(
    data = lr_example,
    results = lr_comprehensive_results,
    performance = list(
      uniform = list(sensitivity = sens_uniform, specificity = spec_uniform, precision = prec_uniform),
      nonuniform = list(sensitivity = sens_nonuniform, specificity = spec_nonuniform, precision = prec_nonuniform)
    )
  ))
}

## === COMPREHENSIVE LOGISTIC REGRESSION DIF ANALYSIS ===
## LR Example Dataset:

# Comprehensive DIF analysis and decision making
demonstrate_comprehensive_dif_analysis <- function() {
  
  cat("=== COMPREHENSIVE DIF ANALYSIS DEMONSTRASIYASI ===\n")
  
  # Create realistic test scenario
  set.seed(5555)
  comprehensive_example <- simulate_dif_data(
    n_focal = 600, n_reference = 900, n_items = 20,
    dif_items = c(3, 7, 12, 16, 18), dif_type = "uniform", dif_size = 1.0
  )
  
  # Add some non-uniform DIF and crossing DIF
  data_matrix <- comprehensive_example$data
  group_vector <- comprehensive_example$group
  theta <- comprehensive_example$theta
  
  # Add non-uniform DIF to items 5 and 14
  for(i in 1:length(theta)) {
    if(group_vector[i] == "Focal") {
      
      # Item 5: Non-uniform favoring high-ability focal
      a_new_5 <- 3.2
      b_new_5 <- -0.2
      prob_new_5 <- exp(a_new_5 * (theta[i] - b_new_5)) / (1 + exp(a_new_5 * (theta[i] - b_new_5)))
      data_matrix[i, 5] <- rbinom(1, 1, prob_new_5)
      
      # Item 14: Crossing DIF
      if(theta[i] < -0.5) {
        prob_new_14 <- exp(0.8 * (theta[i] - 1.5)) / (1 + exp(0.8 * (theta[i] - 1.5)))
      } else {
        prob_new_14 <- exp(2.8 * (theta[i] + 0.8)) / (1 + exp(2.8 * (theta[i] + 0.8)))
      }
      data_matrix[i, 14] <- rbinom(1, 1, prob_new_14)
    }
  }
  
  comprehensive_example$data <- data_matrix
  comprehensive_example$true_params$all_dif_items <- c(3, 5, 7, 12, 14, 16, 18)
  comprehensive_example$true_params$uniform_dif <- c(3, 7, 12, 16, 18)
  comprehensive_example$true_params$nonuniform_dif <- c(5, 14)
  
  cat("Comprehensive Test Scenario:\n")
  cat("Total items:", ncol(data_matrix), "\n")
  cat("Reference group:", sum(group_vector == "Reference"), "\n")
  cat("Focal group:", sum(group_vector == "Focal"), "\n")
  cat("True DIF items:", paste(comprehensive_example$true_params$all_dif_items, collapse = ", "), "\n\n")
  
  # STEP 1: Apply multiple DIF detection methods
  cat("=== STEP 1: MULTIPLE DIF DETECTION METHODS ===\n")
  
  detection_results <- data.frame(
    Item = 1:ncol(data_matrix),
    True_DIF = 1:ncol(data_matrix) %in% comprehensive_example$true_params$all_dif_items
  )
  
  # Method 1: Mantel-Haenszel
  detection_results$MH_Flag <- "No DIF"  # Initialize with default value
  
  if(require(difR, quietly = TRUE)) {
    tryCatch({
      group_numeric <- as.numeric(group_vector) - 1
      mh_results <- difMH(data_matrix, group_numeric, focal.name = 1, match = "score")
      
      detection_results$MH_p <- round(mh_results$p.value, 4)
      detection_results$MH_DeltaMH <- round(mh_results$deltaMH, 3)
      detection_results$MH_Flag <- ifelse(mh_results$p.value < 0.05 & abs(mh_results$deltaMH) >= 1.0, "DIF", "No DIF")
      
    }, error = function(e) {
      cat("MH analysis failed, using default values\n")
      detection_results$MH_p <<- rep(NA, nrow(detection_results))
      detection_results$MH_DeltaMH <<- rep(NA, nrow(detection_results))
      detection_results$MH_Flag <<- rep("No DIF", nrow(detection_results))
    })
  } else {
    cat("difR package not available, using default values\n")
    detection_results$MH_p <- rep(NA, nrow(detection_results))
    detection_results$MH_DeltaMH <- rep(NA, nrow(detection_results))
  }
  
  # Method 2: Logistic Regression
  for(item in 1:ncol(data_matrix)) {
    lr_analysis <- dif_logistic_regression(data_matrix, group_vector, item)
    
    detection_results$LR_Uniform_p[item] <- round(lr_analysis$uniform$p_value, 4)
    detection_results$LR_Uniform_R2[item] <- round(lr_analysis$uniform$effect_size, 4)
    detection_results$LR_NonUniform_p[item] <- round(lr_analysis$nonuniform$p_value, 4)
    detection_results$LR_NonUniform_R2[item] <- round(lr_analysis$nonuniform$effect_size, 4)
  }
  
  # LR DIF flags
  detection_results$LR_Uniform_Flag <- with(detection_results,
    ifelse(LR_Uniform_p < 0.05 & LR_Uniform_R2 >= 0.035, "DIF", "No DIF"))
  
  detection_results$LR_NonUniform_Flag <- with(detection_results,
    ifelse(LR_NonUniform_p < 0.05 & LR_NonUniform_R2 >= 0.035, "DIF", "No DIF"))
  
  # Method 3: IRT-based (simplified)
  detection_results$IRT_Flag <- "No DIF"  # Initialize with default value
  
  if(require(mirt, quietly = TRUE)) {
    tryCatch({
      ref_data <- data_matrix[group_vector == "Reference", ]
      focal_data <- data_matrix[group_vector == "Focal", ]
      
      ref_model <- mirt(ref_data, 1, itemtype = "2PL", verbose = FALSE)
      focal_model <- mirt(focal_data, 1, itemtype = "2PL", verbose = FALSE)
      
      ref_params <- coef(ref_model, simplify = TRUE)$items
      focal_params <- coef(focal_model, simplify = TRUE)$items
      
      difficulty_diff <- abs((focal_params[, "d"] / (-focal_params[, "a1"])) - 
                            (ref_params[, "d"] / (-ref_params[, "a1"])))
      
      detection_results$IRT_DiffDiff <- round(difficulty_diff, 3)
      detection_results$IRT_Flag <- ifelse(difficulty_diff > 0.5, "DIF", "No DIF")
      
    }, error = function(e) {
      cat("IRT analysis failed, using default values\n")
      detection_results$IRT_DiffDiff <<- rep(NA, nrow(detection_results))
      detection_results$IRT_Flag <<- rep("No DIF", nrow(detection_results))
    })
  } else {
    cat("mirt package not available, using default values\n")
    detection_results$IRT_DiffDiff <- rep(NA, nrow(detection_results))
  }
  
  # STEP 2: Create consensus flags
  # Check which method columns exist
  method_cols <- c("MH_Flag", "LR_Uniform_Flag", "LR_NonUniform_Flag", "IRT_Flag")
  existing_method_cols <- method_cols[method_cols %in% names(detection_results)]
  
  if(length(existing_method_cols) > 0) {
    # Create a matrix for the existing method columns
    method_matrix <- as.matrix(detection_results[, existing_method_cols, drop = FALSE])
    # Convert to logical (TRUE for "DIF", FALSE for "No DIF" or NA)
    dif_matrix <- method_matrix == "DIF"
    dif_matrix[is.na(dif_matrix)] <- FALSE
    
    # Count methods flagging DIF
    detection_results$Methods_Flagging <- rowSums(dif_matrix, na.rm = TRUE)
    detection_results$Consensus_DIF <- detection_results$Methods_Flagging >= 2
  } else {
    # If no method columns exist, use LR as fallback
    detection_results$Methods_Flagging <- as.numeric(detection_results$LR_Uniform_Flag == "DIF" | detection_results$LR_NonUniform_Flag == "DIF")
    detection_results$Consensus_DIF <- detection_results$Methods_Flagging >= 1
  }
  
  cat("Detection Results Summary:\n")
  # Show only existing columns in the summary
  summary_cols <- c("Item", "True_DIF", "Methods_Flagging", "Consensus_DIF")
  summary_cols <- c(summary_cols, existing_method_cols)
  summary_cols <- summary_cols[summary_cols %in% names(detection_results)]
  print(detection_results[, summary_cols])
  
  # STEP 3: Effect size evaluation
  cat("\n=== STEP 3: EFFECT SIZE EVALUATION ===\n")
  
  # Create comprehensive effect size summary
  effect_size_summary <- data.frame(
    Item = detection_results$Item,
    MH_DeltaMH = if("MH_DeltaMH" %in% names(detection_results)) detection_results$MH_DeltaMH else NA,
    LR_Uniform_R2 = detection_results$LR_Uniform_R2,
    LR_NonUniform_R2 = detection_results$LR_NonUniform_R2,
    IRT_DiffDiff = if("IRT_DiffDiff" %in% names(detection_results)) detection_results$IRT_DiffDiff else NA
  )
  
  # Classify effect sizes
  effect_size_summary$MH_EffectSize <- ifelse(is.na(effect_size_summary$MH_DeltaMH), "NA",
    ifelse(abs(effect_size_summary$MH_DeltaMH) < 1.0, "Negligible",
           ifelse(abs(effect_size_summary$MH_DeltaMH) < 1.5, "Moderate", "Large")))
  
  effect_size_summary$LR_EffectSize <- ifelse(
    pmax(effect_size_summary$LR_Uniform_R2, effect_size_summary$LR_NonUniform_R2, na.rm = TRUE) < 0.035, "Negligible",
    ifelse(pmax(effect_size_summary$LR_Uniform_R2, effect_size_summary$LR_NonUniform_R2, na.rm = TRUE) < 0.070, "Moderate", "Large"))
  
  cat("Effect Size Summary:\n")
  print(effect_size_summary)
  
  # STEP 4: Content review simulation
  cat("\n=== STEP 4: CONTENT REVIEW AND EXPERT JUDGMENT ===\n")
  
  # Simulate content review results
  set.seed(5555)
  content_review <- data.frame(
    Item = detection_results$Item,
    Content_Issue = sample(c("None", "Cultural Reference", "Language Complexity", "Multiple Strategies", "Format Issue"), 
                          ncol(data_matrix), replace = TRUE, prob = c(0.7, 0.1, 0.1, 0.05, 0.05)),
    Expert_Rating = sample(1:5, ncol(data_matrix), replace = TRUE),
    Revision_Feasible = sample(c("Yes", "No", "Uncertain"), ncol(data_matrix), replace = TRUE, prob = c(0.6, 0.2, 0.2))
  )
  
  # Focus on flagged items
  flagged_items <- which(detection_results$Consensus_DIF)
  
  if(length(flagged_items) > 0) {
    cat("Content Review for Flagged Items:\n")
    print(content_review[flagged_items, ])
  } else {
    cat("No items flagged for content review based on consensus.\n")
  }
  
  # STEP 5: Final decision framework
  cat("\n=== STEP 5: FINAL DECISION FRAMEWORK ===\n")
  
  # Create final recommendations
  final_decisions <- data.frame(
    Item = detection_results$Item,
    Statistical_Evidence = detection_results$Consensus_DIF,
    Effect_Size_Large = (effect_size_summary$MH_EffectSize == "Large" & !is.na(effect_size_summary$MH_EffectSize)) | 
                       (effect_size_summary$LR_EffectSize == "Large" & !is.na(effect_size_summary$LR_EffectSize)),
    Content_Concern = content_review$Content_Issue != "None",
    Expert_Rating_Low = content_review$Expert_Rating <= 2,
    Revision_Possible = content_review$Revision_Feasible == "Yes"
  )
  
  # Decision logic
  final_decisions$Recommendation <- with(final_decisions, {
    ifelse(!Statistical_Evidence & !Content_Concern, "RETAIN",
           ifelse(Statistical_Evidence & Effect_Size_Large & Expert_Rating_Low & !Revision_Possible, "REMOVE",
                  ifelse(Statistical_Evidence & Effect_Size_Large & Revision_Possible, "REVISE",
                         ifelse(Statistical_Evidence & !Effect_Size_Large, "MONITOR", "REVIEW"))))
  })
  
  final_decisions$Action_Priority <- with(final_decisions, {
    ifelse(Recommendation == "REMOVE", "HIGH",
           ifelse(Recommendation == "REVISE", "HIGH",
                  ifelse(Recommendation == "MONITOR", "MEDIUM", "LOW")))
  })
  
  cat("Final Recommendations:\n")
  print(final_decisions[, c("Item", "Statistical_Evidence", "Effect_Size_Large", "Content_Concern", "Recommendation", "Action_Priority")])
  
  # Summary statistics
  cat("\n=== DECISION SUMMARY ===\n")
  decision_summary <- table(final_decisions$Recommendation)
  cat("Decision Distribution:\n")
  print(decision_summary)
  
  high_priority_items <- sum(final_decisions$Action_Priority == "HIGH")
  cat("\nHigh priority items requiring immediate action:", high_priority_items, "\n")
  
  # Performance evaluation
  if(length(comprehensive_example$true_params$all_dif_items) > 0) {
    cat("\n=== OVERALL DETECTION PERFORMANCE ===\n")
    
    true_dif_items <- comprehensive_example$true_params$all_dif_items
    detected_items <- which(detection_results$Consensus_DIF)
    
    tp <- length(intersect(detected_items, true_dif_items))
    fp <- length(setdiff(detected_items, true_dif_items))
    fn <- length(setdiff(true_dif_items, detected_items))
    tn <- ncol(data_matrix) - tp - fp - fn
    
    sensitivity <- tp / (tp + fn)
    specificity <- tn / (tn + fp)
    precision <- if(tp + fp > 0) tp / (tp + fp) else 0
    accuracy <- (tp + tn) / ncol(data_matrix)
    
    cat("Detection Performance Metrics:\n")
    cat("True Positives:", tp, "\n")
    cat("False Positives:", fp, "\n")
    cat("False Negatives:", fn, "\n")
    cat("True Negatives:", tn, "\n")
    cat("Sensitivity:", round(sensitivity, 3), "\n")
    cat("Specificity:", round(specificity, 3), "\n")
    cat("Precision:", round(precision, 3), "\n")
    cat("Accuracy:", round(accuracy, 3), "\n")
  }
  
  return(list(
    data = comprehensive_example,
    detection_results = detection_results,
    effect_size_summary = effect_size_summary,
    content_review = content_review,
    final_decisions = final_decisions,
    decision_summary = decision_summary
  ))
}

# Run comprehensive DIF analysis
comprehensive_analysis_results <- demonstrate_comprehensive_dif_analysis()

## === COMMON PITFALLS AND SOLUTIONS ===
# Common pitfalls and solutions
pitfalls_solutions <- c(
  "**PITFALL 1: Ignoring Effect Sizes**",
  "â€¢ Problem: Focus only on p-values",
  "â€¢ Solution: Always report and interpret effect sizes",
  "â€¢ Guidelines: Use established thresholds (ETS: 0.035, 0.070)",
  "",
  "**PITFALL 2: Single Method Reliance**",
  "â€¢ Problem: Using only one DIF detection method",
  "â€¢ Solution: Apply multiple methods and seek consensus",
  "â€¢ Best Practice: Minimum 2-3 different approaches",
  "",
  "**PITFALL 3: Inadequate Sample Sizes**",
  "â€¢ Problem: Too few observations per group",
  "â€¢ Solution: Plan for adequate power (300+ per group for LR)",
  "â€¢ Alternative: Use simpler methods (MH) with smaller samples",
  "",
  "**PITFALL 4: Neglecting Content Review**",
  "â€¢ Problem: Statistical analysis without expert review",
  "â€¢ Solution: Include content experts in DIF analysis",
  "â€¢ Process: Statistical flagging â†’ content review â†’ decision",
  "",
  "**PITFALL 5: Multiple Testing Issues**",
  "â€¢ Problem: Inflated Type I error with many items",
  "â€¢ Solution: Apply appropriate corrections (Bonferroni, FDR)",
  "â€¢ Balance: Control error rates while maintaining power",
  "",
  "**PITFALL 6: Poor Matching Variables**",
  "â€¢ Problem: Using contaminated total scores",
  "â€¢ Solution: Use purified scores or IRT ability estimates",
  "â€¢ Alternative: Rest scores excluding tested item"
)

for(pitfall in pitfalls_solutions) {
  cat(pitfall, "\n")
}
